    </sec>
    <sec id="s2-s4">
      <title>Drug phenotype-associated substructures</title>
      <p>The phenotype-related substructure is the most important information in structural optimization of drug development to eliminate serious adverse drug reactions (SADR). Here, the database provides researchers with valuable drug action phenotype-related substructure information based on compound-substructure relationships from the PubChem database and substructure-ADR or ATC relationships from our algorithm. The relationship score is calculated as follows:</p>
